treatment:03C187F70D47FFCEFF32FDAEFE09FE48
    cito:cites <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.275865>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.275864>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.275862>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.275863> ;
    dc:creator "Scolaro, José Alejandro; Pincheira-Donoso, Daniel" ;
    dc:title "Phymaturus castillensis Scolaro & Pincheira-Donoso, 2010, sp. nov." ;
    trt:definesTaxonConcept <http://taxon-concept.plazi.org/id/Animalia/Phymaturus_castillensis_Scolaro_2010> ;
    trt:publishedIn <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.275861> ;
    a trt:Treatment .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.275861>
    bibo:endPage "32" ;
    bibo:journal "Zootaxa" ;
    bibo:startPage "17" ;
    bibo:volume "2393" ;
    dc:creator "Scolaro, José Alejandro; Pincheira-Donoso, Daniel" ;
    dc:date "2010" ;
    dc:title "Lizards at the end of the world: Two new species of Phymaturus of the patagonicus clade (Squamata, Liolaemidae) revealed in southern Patagonia of Argentina" ;
    fabio:hasPart <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.275865>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.275864>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.275862>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.275863> ;
    a fabio:JournalArticle .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.275865>
    dc:description "FIGURE 4. Adult males and females of the two new species of Phymaturus of the patagonicus clade proposed in this study. Phymaturus castillensis holotype male (a) and paratype female (c) in dorsal view, and adult paratype male (e) in ventral view. All specimens from the type locality. Phymaturus videlai paratype male (b) and paratype female (d) in dorsal view, and female paratype (f) in ventral view. All from the type locality. (Photos: J. A. Scolaro, November 2008)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/275865/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.275864>
    dc:description "FIGURE 3. Geographic distribution of all known members of the Phymaturus patagonicus clade. Note nonoverlapping geographical ranges of most species. Localities are indicated by numbers, and represent Phymaturus nevadoi (1), P. payuniae (2), P. zapalensis (3), P. tenebrosus (4), P. manuelae (5), P. spurcus (6), P. excelsus (7), P. spectabilis (8), P. agilis (9), P. ceii (10), P. somuncurensis (11), P. calcogaster (12), P. patagonicus (13), P. indistinctus (14), P. v i d e l a i sp. nov. (15), and P. castillensis sp. nov. (16). The wide and scattered geographical distribution shown for P. patagonicus has been considered as the result of several cryptic different species recognized until today as polymorphisms within this species, and many of them are currently under study in order to establish their status within Phymaturus." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/275864/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.275862>
    dc:description "FIGURE 1. Phymaturus species of the patagonicus clade, showing the remarkable diversity of patterns of coloration known within this lineage. Phymaturus agilis (a, male; b, female), P. calcogaster (c, male; d, female), P. ceii (e, male; f, female), P. excelsus (g, male; h, female), P. indistinctus (i, male; j, female), P. manuelae (k, male; l, female), and P. nevadoi (m, male; n, female). (Photos: all J. A. Scolaro, except P. nevadoi, by J. M. Cei)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/275862/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.275863>
    dc:description "FIGURE 2. Phymaturus species of the patagonicus clade (continued from figure 1). Phymaturus patagonicus (a, male; b, female), P. payuniae (c, male; d, female), P. somuncurensis (e, male; f, female), P. spectabilis (g, male; h, female), P. spurcus (i, male; j, female), P. tenebrosus (k, male; l, female), and P. zapalensis (m, male; n, female). (Photos: J. A. Scolaro)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/275863/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

